Three Generals of Mt. Paektu Honored on Occasion of Anniv. of Liberation of Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- At least 150 diplomas of honorary titles, medals, silk banners, gifts and floral baskets were presented to the three generals of Mt. Paektu by the international democratic bodies and at least 50 delegations and representatives of the friendly and solidarity bodies from the different regions and countries that participated in the meeting dedicated to the great persons of Mt. Paektu on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation in August.
 The mayor of Loja City of Ecuador informed a DPRK official concerned of the decision to register President Kim Il Sung,  Kim Jong Suk, anti-Japanese war hero, and leader Kim Jong Il as honorary citizens and present a key to the city to Kim Jong Il and conveyed to the official diplomas of honorary citizenship and the key sent by the city government council according to the decision. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Women's International Democratic Federation registered Kim Jong Suk as its honorary member and presented a certificate of an honorary member to her.
Foreign political and public figures presented silk banners carrying their best wishes to the great persons of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Among them were the international democratic bodies and friendship and solidarity bodies including the International Liaison Committee for the Reunification and Peace in Korea and the secretary general of the International Lawyers' Committee for Supporting the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and the general secretary of the C.C., the Communist Party of Nepal (Marxist-Leninist) who is chairman of the Great Leader Comrade  Kim Il Sung National Memorial Commission, Nepal.
 The Central Committee of the Communist Party of Russia conferred a medal commemorating the 60th anniversary of the victory in the Great Patriotic War in Russia and its certificate to Kim Jong Il and the Association for Friendship with the DPRK having its branches in over 90 countries presented its flag to him and foreign friends presented him with a basket of flowers in the name of the participants in the meeting dedicated to the great persons of Mt. Paektu and other floral baskets wishing him good health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international democratic bodies and the delegations and representatives of the friendly and solidarity bodies from different regions and countries presented to him many gifts carrying their best wishes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairperson of the Women's International Democratic Federation presented Kim Il Sung with a jeweled handcraft "Tree of hope." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Kim Jong Il was presented with precious gifts by foreign bodies and individual figures.
They include the Afro-Asian People's Solidarity Committee of Nepal, the president of the International Association of Democratic Lawyers, the general secretary of the New Left Movement of Peru, the delegation of the China Association for International Friendly Contact and the family of Zhang Weihua, anti-Japanese revolutionary martyr.

U.S. Urged to Implement Joint Statement 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Voices urging the United States to sincerely implement the joint statement agreed upon at the fourth round of the six-party talks are loudly ringing out in south Korea.
 The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification in a statement on Sept. 22 said that if the agreed points of the joint statement are sincerely implemented, the Korean Peninsula will be denuclearized and a new peace mechanism be established in this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But heavyweights of the U.S. are insisting on "north Korea's abandonment of nuclear program first" right after the six-party talks, the statement said, denouncing this as a reckless act of impairing the spirit of the joint statement welcomed all over the world.
 Noting that if the U.S. insists on "north Korea's abandonment of nuclear program first and provision of light water reactors afterward", its consequences will be very serious, it stressed that the U.S. should keep its promise laid down in the joint statement of the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification in south Korea also issued a commentary condemning the U.S. for laying obstacles again in the way of implementing the joint statement. The commentary said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States that is possessed of most numerous nuclear weapons in the world and is plotting to put into practice its preemptive nuclear attack is trying to evade its provision of light water reactors, a substantial guarantee for the north's right to use nuclear energy for a peaceful purpose, recognized by international law. This is diametrically contrary to the spirit of the joint statement called "the spirit of mutual respect and equality". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary strongly urged the U.S. to provide the north with light water reactors (LWRs), the just right and demand of the north as a sovereign state, on the principle of implementing the joint statement with "commitments for commitments" and "action for action". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that the U.S. should stop its plan for mounting a preemptive nuclear attack on the north and expanding the role of the U.S. forces for their permanent presence in the south and implement the joint statement on making joint efforts to establish peace mechanism on the Korean Peninsula and achieve peace and stability in Northeast Asia.

International Maritime Day Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson Thursday observes the International Maritime Day.
 The International Maritime Organization set "International marine transport-deliverer of world trade" as this year's theme and decided to hold various functions at the headquarters of the organization on Sept. 29 to mark the day. 
 It is very important to develop the marine transport worldwide at present, the article says, adding that the organization has taken diverse measures to ensure successful navigation of trading ships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But piracy against ships on voyage is getting more pronounced as the days go by and the U.S. has become evermore undisguised in its moves to put big straits of strategic significance under its military domination under the pretext of combating terrorism, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. military intervention in the maritime field is a wanton violation of the international maritime convention and regulations. Unless it is checked, it will be impossible to develop marine transport and ensure safe navigation of ships.
 In order to develop international trade through marine transport it is necessary to strengthen cooperation among countries and check the U.S. moves to monopolize international sea routes, a treasure common to humankind, to meet its selfish purpose.
 It is the consistent stand of the DPRK government to ensure safe international navigation, preserve sea environment and boost cooperation and exchange among countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will as ever make positive efforts to discharge its mission before the organization as its member.

Intensified Anti-Imperialist Struggle against War Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Imperialists are blatantly perpetrating military intervention and aggression against the progressive countries, persisting in their high-handed and arbitrary practices. This situation requires the world progressive people to wage a dynamic anti-imperialist struggle against war under the banner of defending peace.  
 Rodong Sinmun Thursday observes this in a signed article. It goes on:
 The danger of war is increasing as the days go by in the world and grave obstacles are lying in the way of the people's struggle  for progress and peace in the new century due to the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A struggle against war precisely means an anti-imperialist struggle. 
 Enshrined in the joint slogans issued by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea are the idea and spirit that it is impossible to avert a war nor is it possible to achieve lasting peace without an anti-imperialist struggle. This is entirely just scientific truth. 
 The joint slogans calling for defending peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world from the imperialists' moves for aggression and war are powerfully encouraging all the peace-loving progressives of the world in the struggle for defending peace as they consider the anti-imperialist struggle against war as fundamental conditions for protecting peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unity precisely means strength and provides a sure guarantee for victory. Only when broad strata of peace-loving forces of the world struggle in unity, is it possible to frustrate the war moves of the imperialists and defend peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists are now stepping up their policies of appeasement and deception and threat and blackmail against the anti-imperialist and independent countries. This is nothing but a crafty artifice to break the unity of the anti-imperialist independent forces and destroy them one by one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to achieve the unity among the world peace-loving forces it is necessary to abide by the principle of respect for independence. The anti-imperialist struggle against war is one for defending independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States is the target of the anti-imperialist struggle at present. It is committing brigandish armed invasion against small and weak countries and anti-imperialist independent countries without hesitation, counting on its upper hand of strength. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world people should properly see through the true colors of the U.S. imperialists, the foe of peace and chieftain of war, and courageously struggle to frustrate their moves for aggression and war from a steadfast anti-U.S. stand.

Joint Rally Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- A joint action rally for peace against war and for the withdrawal of the dispatched troops reportedly took place in Seoul on Sept. 24 with the attendance of at least 600 students and members of civic and social organizations of south Korea. 
 Jong Kwang Hun, co-representative of the People's Action against the Dispatch of Troops, Ha Yon Ho, senior member of the Democratic Workers' Party, and other speakers referred to the fact that the south Korean government authorities are pushing ahead with the formation of an equipment unit for the UN peace-keeping activities and examining a proposal for dispatching the UN peace-keeping force without an approval of the National Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding this as an unjust action to continue dispatching the south Korean army to the field for a war of aggression under the pretext of so called "peace-keeping", they called for checking it without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution was read out at the rally. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that though the Jaitun unit was dispatched to Iraq not for reconstruction but for the assistance of the U.S. army, the defense ministry seeks to continue the dispatch of the troops till next year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the unit should be completely pulled back at once, the resolution called for invigorating the drive to oppose the continuance of the dispatch of the troops in the latter half of the year with the beginning of this rally.

U.S. Interference Concerning Withdrawal of Statue of MacArthur in S. Korea under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity of Youth and Students for the Implementation of the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration in south Korea reportedly declared that the reappraisal of MacArthur is a work for the south Korean people to do, not a work for the U.S. to meddle in.
 The organization in a statement issued on Sept. 25 in denunciation of the U.S. interference in the internal affairs concerning the removal of his statue said:
 Members of the U.S. House of Representatives in a letter to the U.S. embassy in Seoul on Sept. 15 openly expressed their complaints, describing the U.S. troops present in south Korea as "liberators" and saying that they can not consent to appraise the hero who commanded the liberation army as a war criminal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement termed it a plain interference in the internal affairs of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is natural that the people are now reappraising MacArthur who massacred numerous innocent civilians and the struggle for withdrawal of his statue is gaining momentum. No countries have built a statue of the man who killed their nation. 
 The U.S. patronage of MacArthur symbolic of aggression and war is a revelation of its plunderous nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anyone who wants to defend the nation should not yield to the U.S. interference but turn out in the struggle for the removal of the statue of MacArthur and the pullback of the U.S. troops.

Huichon Hard Glassware Factory Commissioned
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Huichon, September 28 (KCNA) -- The Huichon Hard Glassware Factory was commissioned with due ceremony on Sept. 28.
 This factory is a praiseworthy gift of labor presented by the workers and technicians of the DPRK to the glorious Workers' Party of Korea on its 60th anniversary.
 The factory covering an area of at least 12,000 square meters has a production building and several annexes. All the production processes ranging from raw material feeding to finishing process are based on the latest science and technology. 
 The factory is capable of producing more than 10 million pieces of quality glassware of beautiful colors per year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il's thanks to the officials and builders who participated in the construction of the factory and its employees were conveyed at the ceremony.
 Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, in his report said that Kim Jong Il indicated ways of building the factory, stressing the need to produce quality hard glassware and send them to the army and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak recalled that Kim Jong Il personally visited the factory last year when it was in trial operation and expressed great satisfaction over the fact that it was built well, as required by the new century and set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines in managing and operating the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appearance of the modern hard glassware factory capable of mass-producing quality glassware is a precious fruition of  Kim Jong Il's wise leadership and his warm love for the people, Pak noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called upon the officials and employees of the factory to operate the factory in full capacity so as to keep its production going at a high rate and supply more quality hard glassware to the army and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the ceremony the participants went round the production processes of the factory.

Farm Machine Production Increases
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Haeju Trailed Farm Machine Factory, a farm-machine production base in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, has manufactured many rice combines and threshers of new type.
 The efficiency of the newly manufactured machines doubles that of the existing ones. It is easy to move them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the factory is also making trailers and various kinds of farm machine accessories urgently needed for the ongoing harvesting and threshing.
 It, founded in October Juche 47(1958), has manufactured various farm machines and accessories for agriculture, stock breeding, pomiculture and sericulture with main emphasis on the production of trailed farm machines, thus greatly contributing to the economic development of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years it has made high-speed rice-seedling transplanters and other farm machines to be sent to co-op farms of South Hwanghae, Kangwon and North Phyongan Provinces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The workers and technicians of the factory are launching mass technical innovation drive in the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance to overcome the economic difficulties.

More Foreigners and Compatriots Come to Enjoy "Arirang"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Foreigners and overseas compatriots are coming here one after another to enjoy the grand gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang".
 Among the arrivals on Sept. 28 were groups of visitors from China, Hong Kong of China, Mongolia, Guinea, the UK and other countries. A group of Russians and a group of Korean residents in Russia arrived here today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They came here by the airliner specially operated by Koryo Airlines to the convenience of foreign guests visiting the DPRK to watch "Arirang". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Audiences are deeply impressed to watch "Arirang" which has been re-depicted as a great masterpiece in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A daily increasing number of groups of visitors are coming to enjoy this extravaganza now under way at the picturesque May Day Stadium in Pyongyang, drawing capacity audience every day.
